@startuml
title Viaverse Roadmap / Release Phases — Master Flow
left to right direction

rectangle "P0 — Foundation\nArchitecture docs\nMonorepo setup\nCI/CD skeleton\nDesign system baseline\nDomain language" as P0
rectangle "P1 — Core Platform Alpha\nIdentity/OTP/social login\nAccount capabilities\nProfiles\nTaxonomy\nRequest creation" as P1
rectangle "P2 — Marketplace Beta\nOffer/quote flow\nJob lifecycle\nChat scoped to job\nNotification inbox\nSearch basics" as P2
rectangle "P3 — Trust + Payment Pilot\nIyzico/TR payment\nEscrow-like flow\nReviews/ratings\nDisputes\nModeration" as P3
rectangle "P4 — Business Launch\nBusiness account\nCatalog/branches/staff\nSubscription trial\nAdmin config\nInsights" as P4
rectangle "P5 — Public Launch TR\nSEO landing\nAds/sponsored\nAnalytics\nSupport/AI helper\nApp store release" as P5
rectangle "P6 — Scale Readiness\nKubernetes hardening\nObservability/SLO\nSecurity/KVKK audit\nLoad tests\nCost controls" as P6
rectangle "P7 — Growth / Global Prep\nLocalization expansion\nStripe/global payments\nRegional config\nAdvanced matching\nML/AI quality" as P7

P0 --> P1 : foundation ready
P1 --> P2 : core flows
P2 --> P3 : transactions
P3 --> P4 : merchant ops
P4 --> P5 : launch pack
P5 --> P6 : stabilize
P6 --> P7 : scale/growth

note bottom
No throwaway MVP. Build a narrow but production-shaped slice first.
Each phase exits with working product, tests, observability, rollback path and updated docs.
end note
@enduml
